<subSubSection lastPageId="131" lastPageNumber="132" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="129.[151,1437,960,2043]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,275,1066,1092]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Larva</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
CUTICULAR COLORATION: Pronotum and abdominal terga I–VI as figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Muller-Liebenau, I." pageId="129" pageNumber="130" pagination="85 - 99" refId="ref65017" refString="Muller-Liebenau, I. (1984 a) Baetidae from Sabah (East Malaysia) (Ephemeroptera). In: Landa, V., Soldan, T. &amp; Tonner, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 4 th International Conference on Ephemeroptera. Institute of Entomology, Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences, Ceske Budejovice, pp. 85 - 99." type="book chapter" year="1984">Müller-Liebenau (1984a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 11).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[151,1437,960,2043]" box="[199,711,1136,1162]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">HYPODERMAL COLORATION: Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[151,1437,960,2043]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
SHAPE: Labrum short, widest at base and narrowed distally (
<figureCitation box="[880,977,1171,1198]" captionStart="FIGURES 624–625" captionStartId="128.[151,264,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1101,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-433@128.[151,1436,1101,1786]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURES 624–625. Centroptella (Chopralla) papuanica sp. n., egg (extracted from holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577630/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Fig. 625</figureCitation>
). Incisor of left mandible terminated with 4 denticles decreasing from most distal to most proximal; incisor of right mandible terminated with 3 denticles of subequal width, without 4th denticle; left and right incisors with outer-ventral denticle (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller-Liebenau, I." box="[1119,1389,1242,1268]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" pagination="85 - 99" refId="ref65017" refString="Muller-Liebenau, I. (1984 a) Baetidae from Sabah (East Malaysia) (Ephemeroptera). In: Landa, V., Soldan, T. &amp; Tonner, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 4 th International Conference on Ephemeroptera. Institute of Entomology, Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences, Ceske Budejovice, pp. 85 - 99." type="book chapter" year="1984">Müller-Liebenau 1984a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5e). Prostheca of left mandible with 3 blunt processes and 2–3 pointed processes. Prostheca of right mandible directed medially or medially-proximally, bifurcate, with longest branch directed medially-proximally or proximally; median margin of right mandible proximad of prostheca with short seta-like processes. Maxillary palp nearly as long as lacinia, 2-segmented, with 2nd much longer than 1st segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[151,1437,960,2043]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Pronotum without protuberances (in contrast to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[744,873,1418,1444]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingridae">
<emphasis box="[744,873,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">C. ingridae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Metanotum with vestiges of hind protoptera (in all 6 individuals examined). Forelegs longest, hind legs shortest; on fore and middle legs tarsus (measured on outer side) as long as tibia; on hind legs tarsus slightly shorter than tibia (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller-Liebenau, I." box="[929,1202,1488,1514]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" pagination="85 - 99" refId="ref65017" refString="Muller-Liebenau, I. (1984 a) Baetidae from Sabah (East Malaysia) (Ephemeroptera). In: Landa, V., Soldan, T. &amp; Tonner, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 4 th International Conference on Ephemeroptera. Institute of Entomology, Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences, Ceske Budejovice, pp. 85 - 99." type="book chapter" year="1984">Müller-Liebenau 1984a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5h). All femora parallel-sided, outer margin straight or slightly concave, inner margin slightly convex. Foreleg without patella-tibial suture, middle and hind legs with patella-tibial suture greatly shifted to apex of tibia [see 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[1133,1274,1559,1585]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[1133,1274,1559,1585]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1279,1318,1559,1585]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" sensu="lato">s. l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(2)] (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller-Liebenau, I." pageId="129" pageNumber="130" pagination="85 - 99" refId="ref65017" refString="Muller-Liebenau, I. (1984 a) Baetidae from Sabah (East Malaysia) (Ephemeroptera). In: Landa, V., Soldan, T. &amp; Tonner, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 4 th International Conference on Ephemeroptera. Institute of Entomology, Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences, Ceske Budejovice, pp. 85 - 99." type="book chapter" year="1984">Müller-Liebenau 1984a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5h). Claw with two rows of 2–5 denticles in each [see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waltz &amp; McCafferty" authorityYear="1987" box="[1063,1178,1594,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Chopralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1063,1178,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Chopralla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(2)] (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller-Liebenau, I." pageId="129" pageNumber="130" pagination="85 - 99" refId="ref65017" refString="Muller-Liebenau, I. (1984 a) Baetidae from Sabah (East Malaysia) (Ephemeroptera). In: Landa, V., Soldan, T. &amp; Tonner, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 4 th International Conference on Ephemeroptera. Institute of Entomology, Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences, Ceske Budejovice, pp. 85 - 99." type="book chapter" year="1984">Müller-Liebenau 1984a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5i).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[151,1437,960,2043]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Denticles on posterior margins of abdominal terga and sterna flat (not conic). Terga I–VIII, without denticles; tergum IX with triangular denticles interrupted medially, behind pair of submedian setae (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1261,1699,1726]" captionStart="FIGURES 626–631" captionStartId="130.[151,264,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-80@130.[151,1436,309,1827]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURES 626–631. Centroptella (Chopralla) pusilla, larva. 626, abdominal tergum IX; 627, subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle; 628, labrum; 629, labrum according to original description (Müller-Liebenau 1984a: fig. 5a) with presumable basal margin added with red line; 630, paraprocts; 631, posterior margin of abdominal tergum X. Abbreviations: gs1–gs3, segments of gonostyli; pgs, larval protogonostylus; usg, unistyliger." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577632/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Fig. 626</figureCitation>
). Posterior projection of abdominal tergum X trapezoid, without denticles or with small denticles on angles only (
<figureCitation box="[1249,1346,1735,1762]" captionStart="FIGURES 626–631" captionStartId="130.[151,264,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-80@130.[151,1436,309,1827]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURES 626–631. Centroptella (Chopralla) pusilla, larva. 626, abdominal tergum IX; 627, subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle; 628, labrum; 629, labrum according to original description (Müller-Liebenau 1984a: fig. 5a) with presumable basal margin added with red line; 630, paraprocts; 631, posterior margin of abdominal tergum X. Abbreviations: gs1–gs3, segments of gonostyli; pgs, larval protogonostylus; usg, unistyliger." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577632/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Fig. 631</figureCitation>
). Sterna I–IV without denticles; sterna V–VIII with regular, small, pointed, triangular denticles. Posterior margin of sternum IX in male without denticles between protogonostyli (
<figureCitation box="[759,858,1805,1832]" captionStart="FIGURES 626–631" captionStartId="130.[151,264,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-80@130.[151,1436,309,1827]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURES 626–631. Centroptella (Chopralla) pusilla, larva. 626, abdominal tergum IX; 627, subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle; 628, labrum; 629, labrum according to original description (Müller-Liebenau 1984a: fig. 5a) with presumable basal margin added with red line; 630, paraprocts; 631, posterior margin of abdominal tergum X. Abbreviations: gs1–gs3, segments of gonostyli; pgs, larval protogonostylus; usg, unistyliger." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577632/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Fig. 627</figureCitation>
). Paraprocts with thin and colorless antero- median apodeme, with large pointed denticles on posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[819,917,1840,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 626–631" captionStartId="130.[151,264,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-80@130.[151,1436,309,1827]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURES 626–631. Centroptella (Chopralla) pusilla, larva. 626, abdominal tergum IX; 627, subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle; 628, labrum; 629, labrum according to original description (Müller-Liebenau 1984a: fig. 5a) with presumable basal margin added with red line; 630, paraprocts; 631, posterior margin of abdominal tergum X. Abbreviations: gs1–gs3, segments of gonostyli; pgs, larval protogonostylus; usg, unistyliger." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577632/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Fig. 630</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[151,1437,960,2043]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Tergalius I narrow, elongate-ellipsoid; other tergalii wider, gradually changing in shape from tergalius II to tergalius VII; each tergalius II–VII, besides costal and anal ribs, with straight and narrow middle rib, located on dorsal surface on background of main trachea (see 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[646,787,1946,1972]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[646,787,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[794,834,1946,1973]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" sensu="lato">s. l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[151,1437,960,2043]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Enlarged denticles on outer side of cercus not large (reaching midlength of next segment), located on every 4th segment and arranged by 1–2 on each side of secondary swimming setal row [see 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[1070,1211,2016,2042]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[1070,1211,2016,2042]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1218,1258,2016,2043]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" sensu="lato">s. l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(3)].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="130.[151,1436,150,285]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
SCALES: Scales on pronotum, mesonotum and protoptera very small (with sockets 3–4 mkm and length 4–5 mkm). Femora, tibiae and tarsi densely covered with colorless, short, oval scales (sockets 5–6 mkm). Scales on abdominal terga numerous, elongate, oval, wider than their sockets (
<figureCitation box="[912,1010,223,250]" captionStart="FIGURES 626–631" captionStartId="130.[151,264,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-80@130.[151,1436,309,1827]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURES 626–631. Centroptella (Chopralla) pusilla, larva. 626, abdominal tergum IX; 627, subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle; 628, labrum; 629, labrum according to original description (Müller-Liebenau 1984a: fig. 5a) with presumable basal margin added with red line; 630, paraprocts; 631, posterior margin of abdominal tergum X. Abbreviations: gs1–gs3, segments of gonostyli; pgs, larval protogonostylus; usg, unistyliger." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577632/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Fig. 626</figureCitation>
). Scales on abdominal sterna, thoracic pleura and metanotum smaller.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577632" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5577632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577632/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" startId="130.[151,264,1850,1874]" targetBox="[151,1436,309,1808]" targetPageId="130">
<paragraph blockId="130.[151,1437,1850,1983]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,366,1850,1874]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">FIGURES 626–631.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller-Liebenau" authorityYear="1984" box="[371,701,1850,1874]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusilla" subGenus="Chopralla">
<emphasis box="[371,498,1850,1874]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Centroptella</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[513,617,1850,1874]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Chopralla</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[632,701,1850,1874]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, larva. 626, abdominal tergum IX; 627, subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle; 628, labrum; 629, labrum according to original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller-Liebenau, I." box="[968,1213,1886,1910]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" pagination="85 - 99" refId="ref65017" refString="Muller-Liebenau, I. (1984 a) Baetidae from Sabah (East Malaysia) (Ephemeroptera). In: Landa, V., Soldan, T. &amp; Tonner, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 4 th International Conference on Ephemeroptera. Institute of Entomology, Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences, Ceske Budejovice, pp. 85 - 99." type="book chapter" year="1984">Müller-Liebenau 1984a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5a) with presumable basal margin added with red line; 630, paraprocts; 631, posterior margin of abdominal tergum X. Abbreviations: gs1–gs3, segments of gonostyli; pgs, larval protogonostylus; usg, unistyliger.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,151,1186]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
STOUT SETAE: Outer side of femur with regular row of 7–13 long, clavate setae and 2 subapical setae of same form (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller-Liebenau, I." box="[221,493,187,213]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" pagination="85 - 99" refId="ref65017" refString="Muller-Liebenau, I. (1984 a) Baetidae from Sabah (East Malaysia) (Ephemeroptera). In: Landa, V., Soldan, T. &amp; Tonner, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 4 th International Conference on Ephemeroptera. Institute of Entomology, Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences, Ceske Budejovice, pp. 85 - 99." type="book chapter" year="1984">Müller-Liebenau 1984a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5h). Inner-anterior side of each femur with small, stout, blunt setae; no longer setae on inner-anterior side of fore femur. Tibia and tarsus with stout setae on inner side. Outer-apical seta of tibia blunt and elongate (as in 
<figureCitation box="[433,531,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURES 364–368" captionStartId="80.[151,264,1703,1727]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1679]" captionTargetId="figure-27@80.[151,1436,181,1679]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURES 364–368. Centroptella (Crassolus) ludmilae sp. n., larval exuviae. 364, apex of fore tibia (arrow shows outer-apical seta); 365, abdominal tergum V; 366, abdominal tergum III of holotype (MA, medioanterior sigilla; MP, medioposterior sigilla); 367, abdominal tergum X; 368, female abdominal sternum IX and paraprocts." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577542/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Fig. 364</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="131" pageNumber="132" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,151,1186]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<collectionCode box="[199,280,295,321]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">LONG</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode box="[293,355,295,321]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">FINE</collectionCode>
SETAE: Bifurcate setae of metasternum (i) (see 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[919,1060,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[919,1060,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1069,1109,295,322]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" sensu="lato">s. l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) form pair of dense, regular rows partly with contiguous sockets (as in 
<figureCitation box="[648,748,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 512–517" captionStartId="107.[151,264,1802,1826]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1778]" captionTargetId="figure-20@107.[151,1436,181,1778]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="FIGURES 512–517. Centroptella (Chopralla) ghatensis sp. n., exuviae of larval thorax. 512–513, scales and bifurcate setae on anterior part of mesonotum (corresponding to e on Fig. 14); 514–517, bifurcate setae on thoracic sternum (corresponding to h and i on Fig. 15)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577594/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Fig. 517</figureCitation>
). Posterior arm of U-shaped row of long setae on fore- and middle leg situated across tibia, on hind leg longitudinal [see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waltz &amp; McCafferty" authorityYear="1987" box="[871,986,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Chopralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[871,986,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Chopralla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(1)] (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller-Liebenau, I." box="[1056,1330,367,393]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" pagination="85 - 99" refId="ref65017" refString="Muller-Liebenau, I. (1984 a) Baetidae from Sabah (East Malaysia) (Ephemeroptera). In: Landa, V., Soldan, T. &amp; Tonner, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 4 th International Conference on Ephemeroptera. Institute of Entomology, Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences, Ceske Budejovice, pp. 85 - 99." type="book chapter" year="1984">Müller-Liebenau 1984a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5h). Dorsal side of each tarsus with long, fine setae situated irregularly and partly forming two longitudinal rows (as in 
<figureCitation box="[151,309,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 560–565" captionStartId="117.[151,264,1920,1944]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,434,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-128@117.[164,1423,417,1897]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="FIGURES 560–565. Centroptella (Chopralla) rufostriata sp. n., larva. 560–561, fore and middle tibiae, anterior view (setae and sutures on opposite side shown by interrupted lines); 562–563, hind tibia and tarsus, anterior and outer view (bases of long, fine setae shown as rings). 564, abdominal tergum IX; 565, abdominal sternum VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577610" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577610/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Figs 562–563</figureCitation>
; see 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[362,503,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[362,503,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[510,550,439,466]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" sensu="lato">s. l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). Tergum VII with pair of fine, V-shaped setae sublaterally (g) (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1326,1424,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 598–606" captionStartId="124.[151,264,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,273,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-72@124.[164,1423,273,1876]" captionTargetPageId="124" captionText="FIGURES 598–606. Centroptella (Chopralla) papuanica sp. n., larval exuviae (holotype). 598, abdomen; 599, pronotum and mesonotum; 600, area of pronotum close to median suture with bifurcate seta corresponding to a on Fig. 14; 601, scale on metanotum with same magnification; 602, abdominal sternum VI and enlarged scales; 603, abdominal sternum IX and enlarged scales; 604, labrum; 605, labium; 606, abdominal terga VIII–IX and enlarged scales." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577622/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Fig. 604</figureCitation>
). Each sternum IV–V with pair of regular, transverse rows of long, fine, bifurcate setae with spaced sockets (j); other sterna either without such setae, or with few setae irregularly situated [see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waltz &amp; McCafferty" authorityYear="1987" box="[987,1102,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Chopralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[987,1102,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Chopralla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(4)].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,151,1186]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<collectionCode box="[199,278,547,573]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">MALE</collectionCode>
GENITALIA IN LARVA: In last larval instar, developing subimaginal gonostyli folded under larval cuticle in « 
<taxonomicName box="[280,411,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Nigrobaetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[280,411,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Nigrobaetis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<typeStatus box="[418,469,583,609]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">type</typeStatus>
» pose, with 2nd and 3rd segments directed caudally and inserted into previous ones (
<figureCitation box="[160,255,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURES 626–631" captionStartId="130.[151,264,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-80@130.[151,1436,309,1827]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURES 626–631. Centroptella (Chopralla) pusilla, larva. 626, abdominal tergum IX; 627, subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle; 628, labrum; 629, labrum according to original description (Müller-Liebenau 1984a: fig. 5a) with presumable basal margin added with red line; 630, paraprocts; 631, posterior margin of abdominal tergum X. Abbreviations: gs1–gs3, segments of gonostyli; pgs, larval protogonostylus; usg, unistyliger." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577632/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Fig. 627</figureCitation>
) [see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waltz &amp; McCafferty" authorityYear="1987" box="[322,437,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Chopralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[322,437,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Chopralla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5)].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="131" pageNumber="132" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,151,1186]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,654,681]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Subimago.</emphasis>
TEXTURE: On all legs all tarsal segments entirely covered with pointed microlepides (as in 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 387–392" captionStartId="84.[151,264,1786,1810]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-27@84.[151,1436,181,1762]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURES 387–392. Centroptella (Crassolus) ludmilae sp. n. 387–388, female imago; 389, exuviae of subimaginal pleuron; 390, exuviae of subimaginal mesonotum; 391, exuviae of female subimaginal fore and hind legs. Abbreviations: T1–T5, tarsomeres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577550" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577550/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Fig. 391</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,151,1186]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,726,753]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Imago, male.</emphasis>
Unknown. Judging by subimaginal leg developed under larval cuticle, tarsus of middle and hind legs with 1 apical spine on initial 3rd tarsomere (next after 1st+2nd tarsomere); sterno-styligeral muscle present [see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waltz &amp; McCafferty" authorityYear="1987" box="[151,266,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Chopralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,266,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Chopralla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(7)].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,151,1186]" box="[199,498,834,861]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,373,834,861]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Imago, female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,151,1186]" box="[199,378,871,897]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,246,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Egg</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,151,1186]" box="[199,648,906,933]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,906,932]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Dimension.</emphasis>
Body length about 
<quantity box="[555,644,906,933]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="131" pageNumber="132" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,151,1186]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,942,968]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Comments.</emphasis>
In the original description, labrum is figured as relatively long, with unusual shape of lateral sides (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller-Liebenau, I." box="[159,431,979,1005]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" pagination="85 - 99" refId="ref65017" refString="Muller-Liebenau, I. (1984 a) Baetidae from Sabah (East Malaysia) (Ephemeroptera). In: Landa, V., Soldan, T. &amp; Tonner, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 4 th International Conference on Ephemeroptera. Institute of Entomology, Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences, Ceske Budejovice, pp. 85 - 99." type="book chapter" year="1984">Müller-Liebenau 1984a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5a). 
<typeStatus box="[543,599,979,1005]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Type</typeStatus>
specimens were kept in Purdue University (
<collectingCountry box="[1109,1170,979,1005]" name="United States of America" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">USA</collectingCountry>
), but now are probably missing (
<collectorName box="[254,376,1015,1041]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">L. Jacobus</collectorName>
, personal communication). My determination of the specimens examined as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller-Liebenau" authorityYear="1984" box="[1232,1340,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis box="[1232,1340,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">C. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on the assumption that Müller-Liebenau took the internal arms of labrum for lateral-proximal margins of the labrum (
<figureCitation box="[159,319,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURES 626–631" captionStartId="130.[151,264,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-80@130.[151,1436,309,1827]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURES 626–631. Centroptella (Chopralla) pusilla, larva. 626, abdominal tergum IX; 627, subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle; 628, labrum; 629, labrum according to original description (Müller-Liebenau 1984a: fig. 5a) with presumable basal margin added with red line; 630, paraprocts; 631, posterior margin of abdominal tergum X. Abbreviations: gs1–gs3, segments of gonostyli; pgs, larval protogonostylus; usg, unistyliger." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577632/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Figs 628–629</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="131" pageNumber="132" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,151,1186]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1122,1148]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Distribution.</emphasis>
Borneo. 
<bibRefCitation author="Selvakumar, C. &amp; Kubendran, T. &amp; Chandra, K. &amp; Sidhu, A. K." box="[458,740,1123,1149]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" pagination="373 - 376" refId="ref65332" refString="Selvakumar, C., Kubendran, T., Chandra, K. &amp; Sidhu, A. K. (2017) First record of the genus Bungona (Harker 1957) (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae) and range extension of two species belonging to Bungona in India. Journal of Entomological Research, 41 (4), 373 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.5958 / 0974 - 4576.2017.00059.7" type="journal article" year="2017">
Selvakumar 
<emphasis box="[600,650,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">et al</emphasis>
. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
erroneously reported 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller-Liebenau" authorityYear="1984" box="[989,1099,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis box="[989,1099,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">C. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1274,1335,1123,1149]" name="India" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">India</collectingCountry>
; actually the larvae from 
